track.name: This Girl (Kungs vs. Cookin' on 3 Burners)

album.title: 100% Tubes de l'Eté 2017 (Tous Les Hits Actuels, Disco-Funk, Années 80, Party, Soleil de l'Été)

wiki.summary: "This Girl" is a song performed by French DJ and producer Kungs (Valentin Brunel) with Australian funk trio Cookin' on 3 Burners. It is a remix of Cookin' on 3 Burners' original song, with vocals by Kylie Auldist. It was released on 19 February 2016 as a digital download by House of Barclay. It was successful across Europe, reaching number 1 in France and Germany. The song was performed by Kungs with the vocalist Mel Sugar on the French television show Le Petit Journal on 24 March. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "This Girl" is a song performed by French DJ and producer Kungs (Valentin Brunel) with Australian funk trio Cookin' on 3 Burners. It is a remix of Cookin' on 3 Burners' original song, with vocals by Kylie Auldist. It was released on 19 February 2016 as a digital download by House of Barclay. It was successful across Europe, reaching number 1 in France and Germany. The song was performed by Kungs with the vocalist Mel Sugar on the French television show Le Petit Journal on 24 March. An EP featuring an extended mix of the track, two remixes and a solo track by Kungs titled "Milos" was released on iTunes on 26 March. Read more on Last.fm.
